  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 200C and mix flour, sugar, and bicarbonate of soda in a bowl.",
    "Add the cold butter to the flour mixture and rub until it resembles fine crumbs.",
    "Stir in cold water to form a dough, then refrigerate for 15 minutes.",
    "Roll out the dough to fit a 23cm tart tin and press it into the tin, trimming the edges.",
    "Combine sliced apples with brown sugar, cinnamon, and ginger in a bowl.",
    "Fill the pastry with the apple mixture, ensuring it is evenly spread.",
    "Bake the pie for 25 minutes or until the crust is golden and the apples are tender.",
    "While the pie bakes, mix apricot jam with 1 tbsp water and spoon over the hot pie, then return to the oven for 5 more minutes to set the glaze.",
    "Peel and boil the potatoes until soft, then mash with butter, oat milk, salt, and a pinch of bicarbonate of soda for fluffiness.",
    "Serve a slice of the glazed apple pie alongside a generous portion of the creamy mash."
  ],
